cle racer]]. He finished twice on the podium of the [[Tour de France]], with a third place in 1956 and in 1960. In both these years, he wore the yellow jersey as the leader of the [[general classification in the Tour de France|general classification]].\n\n== Major victories ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1955\n: 1st in Tour of Morocco\n;1956\n: 1st stage [[Four Days of Dunkirk]]\n: 4th stage Four Days of Dunkirk\n: Winner Four Days of Dunkirk\n;1957\n: 3rd stage [[Paris\u2013Nice]]\n: 7th stage [[Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n;1958\n: Tour du Tessin\n;1961\n: Fl\u00e8che Hesbignonne Evernijs (Cras Avernas)\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Major endings ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1955\n: 5th in de [[La Fl\u00e8che Wallonne]]\n: 5th in [[Li\u00e8ge\u2013Bastogne\u2013Li\u00e8ge]]\n;1956\n: 3rd in the [[1956 Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n;1957\n: 3rd in [[Paris\u2013Brussels]]\n;1958\n: 4th in the [[1958 Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n;1959\n: 2nd place in the [[Belgian]] national championship\n;1960\n: 3rd in the [[1960 Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Tour de France results==\n*[[1953 Tour de France|1953]] \u2013 45th\n*[[1955 Tour de France|1955]] \u2013 28th\n*[[1956 Tour de France|1956]] \u2013 3rd, wearing [[yellow jersey]] for three days\n*[[1957 Tour de France|1957]] \u2013 9th\n*[[1958 Tour de France|1958]] \u2013 4th\n*[[1959 Tour de France|1959]] \u2013 7th\n*[[1960 Tour de France|1960]] \u2013 3rd, wearing [[yellow jersey]] for four days\n*[[1961 Tour de France|1961]] \u2013 10th\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070425035721/http://www.memoire-du-cyclisme.net/palmares/adriaensens_jan.php Palmares {{in lang|fr}}]\n*{{Cycling archives|69}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Adriaensens, Jan}}\n[[Category:Belgian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Belgian Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a stage winners]]\n[[Category:2018 deaths]]\n[[Category:1932 births]]\n[[Category:People from Willebroek]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Antwerp (province)]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n{{Belgium-cycling-bio-1930s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Jan Adriaensens\n| image         =\n| fullname      = Cesar Jan Adriaensens\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1932|06|06}}\n| birth_place   = [[Willebroek]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date    = {{death date and age|df=yes|2018|10|02|1932|06|06}}\n| death_place   = \n| height        =\n| weight        =\n| currentteam   =\n| discipline    = Road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyears1     = 1952\u20131953\n| proteam1      = Libertas\n| proyears2     = 1953\n| proteam2      = Rochet\u2013Dunlop\n| proyears3     = 1954\n| proteam3      = Libertas\u2013Huret\n| proyears4     = {{0}}\n| proteam4      = Plume\u2013Vainqueur\n| proyears5     = {{0}}\n| proteam5      = Dossche Sport\n| proyears6     = {{0}}\n| proteam6      = l'Express\n| proyears7     = {{0}}\n| proteam7      = Rochet\u2013Dunlop\n| proyears8     = {{0}}\n| proteam8      = Alpa\n| proyears9     = 1955\n| proteam9      = Libertas\u2013Huret\n| proyears10    = {{0}}\n| proteam10     = Terrot\u2013Hutchinson\n| proyears11    = {{0}}\n| proteam11     = Plume\u2013Vainqueur\n| proyears12    = 1956\n| proteam12     = Mercier\u2013BP\u2013Hutchinson\n| proyears13    = 1957\n| proteam13     = Carpano\u2013Coppi\n| proyears14    = 1958\n| proteam14     = Carpano\n| proyears15    = 1959\n| proteam15     = Elv\u00e9\u2013Peugeot\n| proyears16    = {{0}}\n| proteam16     = Peugeot\u2013BP\u2013Dunlop\n| proyears17    = 1960\n| proteam17     = Philco\n| proyears18    = 1961\n| proteam18     = Groene Leeuw\u2013SAS\u2013Sinalco\n| majorwins     = [[Four Days of Dunkirk]] (1956)\n}}\n\n'''Jan (Cesar Jan) Adriaensens''' (born 6 June 1932 in [[Willebroek]]<ref>[http://memoire-du-cyclisme.net/palmares/adriaensens_jan.php memoir