{"title_page": "Military Revolutionary Committee", "text_new": "[[File:Milrevkom proclamation.jpg|thumb|Facsimile of the [[Petrograd Military Revolutionary Committee]] proclamation of the disbanding of the [[Russian Provisional Government]]]]\n\nThe '''Military Revolutionary Committee''' ({{lang-ru|\u0412\u043e\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e-\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u043b\u044e\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442}}, {{lang|ru-latn|Voyenn\u043e-revolyutsionny komitet}}), was the name for military organs created by the Bolsheviks under [[Soviet (council)|the soviets]] in preparation for the [[October Revolution]] (October 1917 \u2013 March 1918).<ref name=\"GSE\">[http://bse.sci-lib.com/article005983.html Military Revolutionary Committees]. [[Great Soviet Encyclopedia]].</ref> The committees were powerful directing bodies of revolt, installing and securing the Soviet power. They executed a role of provisional extraordinary organs of Proletariat power.\n\nThe most notable ones were those of the [[Petrograd Soviet]], the Moscow Soviet, and at [[Stavka]]. The [[Petrograd Military Revolutionary Committee]] was created on {{OldStyleDate|29 October|1917|16 October}}.<ref>[http://www.marxist.net/trotsky/russia/lessons.htm#6 Trotsky, Leon, ''Lessons of October'']: \"On October 16th the Military Revolutionary Committee was created, the legal Soviet organ of insurrection.\" Accessed 27 August 2007</ref>\n\n==Creation==\nThe idea for organization of the armed revolt battle center belongs to [[Lenin]].<ref name=\"GSE\"/> In his letter \"Marxism and Revolt\" directed to the [[Central Committee of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union|Central Committee of RSDLP(b)]] in September 1917, he putting on the agenda the task of preparing an armed uprising wrote:\n{{cquote|And to treat the revolt in a Marxist way, that is, as an art, we at the same time, without losing a moment, must organize headquarters of the insurgent groups ...}}<ref name=\"GSE\"/>\n\nThe decision of [[Central Committee of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union|Central Committee of RSDLP(b)]] of October 23 and 29, 1917 on enhanced preparation for the armed revolt hastened the creation of uprising bodies at central and local levels. The MRC were elected from representatives of the [[Bolshevik]]s' party, [[workers' council|soviets]], factory or [[soldier committees]], [[Bolshevik Military Organizations]] (Voyenka), [[Red Guards (Russia)|Red Guards]], and others.<ref name=\"GSE\"/> The committees were of various levels such as gubernial, city, county, district, volost; while in the Army were frontlines, army, corps, division, and regimental. On occasions the functions of the Military Revolutionary Committee were performed by [[Revolutionary committee (Soviet Union)|revolutionary committees]]. The military revolutionary committees were not uniform in terms of their social and party composition, however most of them were predominantly represented by [[bolsheviks]].\n\nThe first headquarters of armed uprising became the [[Petrograd Military Revolutionary Committee]] that was created by the [[Petrograd Soviet]] on October 25, 1917.<ref name=\"GSE\"/> Prior to a victorious moment of the uprising in Petrograd, there were over 40 Military Revolutionary Committees in the country the main activity of which was military and technical preparations for the forthcoming revolt.\n\n==List of military revolutionary committees==\nDuring the \"Triumphant advance of Soviet power\" there was a mass establishment of MRCs. Many MRCs appeared on initiative of the arrived delegates of the [[All-Russian Congress of Soviets|2nd All-Russian Congress of Soviets]]. Big squad of commissars, emissaries, agitators was sent to various country's regions by the Petrograd MRC on direction of the [[Central Committee of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union|Central Committee of RSDLP(b)]].<ref name=\"GSE\"/> The Bolshevik's party composed the committees of experienced organizers.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Creation date !! Name !! Head (composition) !! Notes\n|-\n| October 29 || [[Petrograd Military Revolutionary Committee|Petrograd MRC]] || [[Pavel Lazimir]] ([[Andrei Bubnov]], [[Moisei Uritsky]], [[Yakov Sverdlov]], [[Felix Dzerzhinsky]], [[Joseph Stalin]])<ref>David R. Shearer & Vladimir Khaustov, Stalin and the Lubianka: A Documentary History of the Political Police and Security Organs in the Soviet Union, 1922\u20131953\n</ref> || \n|-\n| October 31 || 12th Army MRC || Ya. Cherin ({{ill|Karl Gailis|ru|\u0413\u0430\u0439\u043b\u0438\u0441, \u041a\u0430\u0440\u043b \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}},<ref>[http://www.istoriacccr.ru/gailis_karl_andreevi.html Gailis Karl Andreyevich] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121031103531/http://www.istoriacccr.ru/gailis_karl_andreevi.html |date=2012-10-31 }}</ref> {{ill|J\u0101nis Kr\u016bmi\u0146\u0161-Pil\u0101ts|lv}})<ref>[http://globalpedia.ru/people.php?id=9915&category=55 Krumin, Janis]</ref>|| until November 8, 1917 existed illegally in [[C\u0113sis]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2| November 4 || Estland MRC || {{ill|Ivan Rabchinsky|ru|\u0420\u0430\u0431\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439, \u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}}<ref>[http://bse.sci-lib.com/article094729.html Rabchinsky, Ivan Vasilyevich]. [[Great Soviet Encyclopedia]]</ref> ([[Jaan Anvelt]], [[Viktor Kingissepp]]) || \n|-\n| Pskov MRC || {{ill|Vasili Panyushkin|ru|\u041f\u0430\u043d\u044e\u0448\u043a\u0438\u043d, \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0439 \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0438\u0447}} || Northern Front (from November 8, 1917)\n|-\n| rowspan=2| November 7 || {{ill|Moscow Military Revolutionary Committee|lt=Moscow MRC|ru|\u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0432\u043e\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e-\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u043b\u044e\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442}} || {{ill|Grigory Usievich|ru|\u0423\u0441\u0438\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447, \u0413\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}} ([[Nikolay Muralov]], {{ill|J\u0101nis Pie\u010de|lv}}, {{ill|Aleksandr Arosev|ru|\u0410\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0432, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440 \u042f\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}}, [[Vladimir Smirnov (politician)|Vladimir Smirnov]])|| \n|-\n| Voronezh revkom || {{ill|Alexey Sergeevich Moiseyev|ru|\u041c\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0435\u0435\u0432, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439 \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}} || \n|-\n| November 8 || Ryazan MRC || {{ill|Arkady Syromyatnikov|ru|\u0421\u044b\u0440\u043e\u043c\u044f\u0442\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432, \u0410\u0440\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0438\u0439 \u0421\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}} || \n|-\n| rowspan=3| November 9 || Minsk MRC || [[Aleksandr Myasnikyan]] ({{ill|Moisei Kalmanovich|ru|\u041a\u0430\u043b\u043c\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447, \u041c\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0435\u0439 \u0418\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0444\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}}, [[Vilhelms Knori\u0146\u0161]], {{ill|K\u0101rlis Landers|ru|\u041b\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0435\u0440, \u041a\u0430\u0440\u043b \u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}}) || Western Front and Northwestern Region (later)\n|-\n| Samara MRC || [[Valerian Kuybyshev]] || \n|-\n| Tula revkom || [[Grigory Kaminsky]] || \n|-\n| November 10 || Tom MRC || {{ill|Aleksei Belenets|ru|\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0446, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439 \u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}}<ref>[http://www.admin.tomsk.ru/pages/city_5_citizens_belenez Aleksei Belenets]</ref> || \n|-\n| rowspan=2| November 11 || Kiev MRC || {{ill|Leonid Pyatakov|ru|\u041f\u044f\u0442\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0432, \u041b\u0435\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0434 \u041b\u0435\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}}<ref>[http://www.peoples.ru/state/revolutionary/leonid_pyatakov/ Leonid Pyatakov]</ref> ([[Andriy Ivanov]], [[Volodymyr Zatonsky]], {{ill|Oleksandr Horvits|ru|\u0413\u043e\u0440\u0432\u0438\u0446, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440 \u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}})<ref>[http://bse.chemport.ru/gorvits_aleksandr_borisovich.shtml Horvits Oleksandr] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150120204129/http://bse.chemport.ru/gorvits_aleksandr_borisovich.shtml |date=2015-01-20 }}. [[Great Soviet Encyclopedia]]</ref> || recreated as Kiev revkom on January 28, 1918\n|-\n| Smolensk revkom || S. Ioffe || \n|-\n| November 21 || Dagestan MRC || {{ill|Ullubi Buinaksky|ru|\u0411\u0443\u0439\u043d\u0430\u043a\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439, \u0423\u043b\u043b\u0443\u0431\u0438\u0439 \u0414\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}} || \n|-\n| November 27 || Orenburg MRC || {{ill|Samuil Tsvilling|ru|\u0426\u0432\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0433, \u0421\u0430\u043c\u0443\u0438\u043b \u041c\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}} || \n|-\n| December 1 || Southwestern Front MRC || G. Razzhivin ({{ill|Vasili Kikvidze|ru|\u041a\u0438\u043a\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0437\u0435, \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0439 \u0418\u0441\u0438\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}}) || \n|-\n| December 15 || Romanian Front MRC || {{ill|Pyotr Baranov|ru|\u0411\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432, \u041f\u0451\u0442\u0440 \u0418\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}} ({{ill|Aleksandr Krusser|ru|\u041a\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0435\u0440, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440 \u0421\u0435\u043c\u0451\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}}, {{ill|Vladimir Yudovsky|ru|\u042e\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439, \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u0413\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0440\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}}) || \n|-\n| December 20 || Barnaul MRC || {{ill|Matvei Tsaplin|ru|\u0426\u0430\u043f\u043b\u0438\u043d, \u041c\u0430\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0439 \u041a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}} || \n|-\n| December 23 || Kharkov MRC || [[Fyodor Sergeyev|Comrade Artyom]] ([[Valery Mezhlauk]], {{ill|Moisei Rukhimovich|ru|\u0420\u0443\u0445\u0438\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447, \u041c\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0435\u0439 \u041b\u044c\u0432\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}}) || \n|-\n| ??? || Yekaterinoslav MRC || [[Nikolay Krestinsky]] || \n|-\n| ??? || Vinnitsa MRC || {{ill|Nikolai Tarnogrodsky|uk|\u0422\u0430\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0433\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430 \u041f\u0430\u0432\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}}<ref>[http://bse-soviet-encyclopedia.info/%D0%91%D0%BE%D0%BB%D1%8C%D1%88%D0%B0%D1%8F_%D0%A1%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B5%D1%82%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B0%D1%8F_%D1%8D%D0%BD%D1%86%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%BF%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%B8%D1%8F/87523/%D0%A2%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B3%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B4%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8%D0%B9_%D0%9D%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%BB%D0%B0%D0%B9_%D0%9F%D0%B0%D0%B2%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%87 Tarnogrodsky Nikolai] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150123150259/http://bse-soviet-encyclopedia.info/%D0%91%D0%BE%D0%BB%D1%8C%D1%88%D0%B0%D1%8F_%D0%A1%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B5%D1%82%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B0%D1%8F_%D1%8D%D0%BD%D1%86%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%BF%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%B8%D1%8F/87523/%D0%A2%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B3%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B4%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8%D0%B9_%D0%9D%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%BB%D0%B0%D0%B9_%D0%9F%D0%B0%D0%B2%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%87 |date=2015-01-23 }}</ref> || \n|-\n| ??? || Odessa MRC || {{ill|Vladimir Yudovsky|ru|\u042e\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439, \u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0440 \u0413\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0440\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}} || \n|-\n| ??? || [[Shuya, Ivanovo Oblast|Shuya]] MRC || [[Mikhail Frunze]] || \n|-\n| ??? || Simferopol MRC || {{ill|J\u0101nis Miller|ru|\u041c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0435\u0440, \u0416\u0430\u043d}} || \n|-\n| December 29 || Sevastopol revkom || [[Yuri Gaven]]\n|-\n| January || Astrakhan revkom || {{ill|Mina Aristov|ru|\u0410\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432, \u041c\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u041b\u044c\u0432\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}}<ref>[https://archive.is/20130410002524/http://astrahanfoto.livejournal.com/130166.html Mina Aristov]</ref> || \n|-\n| January 10 || Caucasus Army MRC || [[Grigory Korganov]] ({{ill|Boris Sheboldayevru|ru|\u0428\u0435\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0434\u0430\u0435\u0432, \u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}}) || \n|-\n| January 23 || Don MRC || {{ill|Fyodor Podtyolkov|ru|\u041f\u043e\u0434\u0442\u0451\u043b\u043a\u043e\u0432, \u0424\u0451\u0434\u043e\u0440 \u0413\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0440\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}} ({{ill|Mikhail Krivoshlykov|ru|\u041a\u0440\u0438\u0432\u043e\u0448\u043b\u044b\u043a\u043e\u0432, \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}})<ref>[http://dic.academic.ru/dic.nsf/sie/8890/%D0%9A%D0%A0%D0%98%D0%92%D0%9E%D0%A8%D0%9B%D0%AB%D0%9A%D0%9E%D0%92 Krivoshlykov Mikhail]. [[Soviet Historical Encyclopedia]].</ref> || \n|-\n| January 30 || Kuban - Black Sea MRC || {{ill|Yan Poluyan|ru|\u041f\u043e\u043b\u0443\u044f\u043d, \u042f\u043d \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}} || \n|-\n| March 2 || Semirechye MRC || {{ill|Pavel Vinogradov|ru|\u0412\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u043e\u0432, \u041f\u0430\u0432\u0435\u043b \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0439\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}} || \n|}\n\n==Influence==\nIn the weeks following the October insurrection, military revolutionary committees based on the MRC of Petrograd were set up throughout the other soviets and helped cement [[Bolshevik]] control.  These other MRCs were formed by locals but agents from the Petrograd MRC were often in positions to give advice or direction.  By the end of October 1917, representatives from the Petrograd MRC were on assignments in at least forty-four cities as well as 113 military units throughout [[Russia]], [[Turkestan]], and [[the Caucasus]].<ref>Rigby, pp. 42-43</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Revolutionary Military Council]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*[[Albert Resis|Resis, Albert]] (July 1977).  Lenin on Freedom of the Press.  Russian Review, Vol. 36, No. 3, pp.&nbsp;274\u2013296.\n*Rigby, T.H. (Jan. 1974). The First Proletarian Government. British Journal of Political Science, Vol. 4, No. 1, pp.&nbsp;37\u201351.\n*Utechin, S.V.  (Oct. 1958).  Bolsheviks and Their Allies after 1917:  The Ideological Pattern.  Soviet Studies, Vol. 10, No. 2, pp.&nbsp;113\u2013135.\n*Lenin, V.I. ''Marxism and Revolt. Full collection of articles'' (\u041c\u0430\u0440\u043a\u0441\u0438\u0437\u043c \u0438 \u0432\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435, \u041f\u043e\u043b\u043d. \u0441\u043e\u0431\u0440. \u0441\u043e\u0447.). Ed. 5. Vol. 34\n*''Questionnaires of councils of the Central Industrial district'' (October 1917 \u2013 January 1918). \"Historical Archives\". 1960\n\n{{Russian Revolution 1917|state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Bolshevik uprisings]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Milrevkom proclamation.jpg|thumb|Facsimile of the [[Petrograd Military Revolutionary Committee]] proclamation of the disbanding of the [[Russian Provisional Government]]]]\n\nThe '''Military Revolutionary Committee''' ({{lang-ru|\u0412\u043e\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e-\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u043b\u044e\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442}}, {{lang|ru-latn|Voyenn\u043e-revolyutsionny komitet}}), was the name for military organs created by the Bolsheviks under [[Soviet (council)|the soviets]] in preparation for the [[October Revolution]] (October 1917 \u2013 March 1918).<ref name=\"GSE\">[http://bse.sci-lib.com/article005983.html Military Revolutionary Committees]. [[Great Soviet Encyclopedia]].</ref> The committees were powerful directing bodies of revolt, installing and securing the Soviet power. They executed a role of provisional extraordinary organs of Proletariat power.\n\nThe most notable ones were those of the [[Petrograd Soviet]], the Moscow Soviet, and at [[Stavka]]. The [[Petrograd Military Revolutionary Committee]] was created on {{OldStyleDate|29 October|1917|16 October}}.<ref>[http://www.marxist.net/trotsky/russia/lessons.htm#6 Trotsky, Leon, ''Lessons of October'']: \"On October 16th the Military Revolutionary Committee was created, the legal Soviet organ of insurrection.\" Accessed 27 August 2007</ref>\n\n==Creation==\nThe idea for organization of the armed revolt battle center belongs to [[Lenin]].<ref name=\"GSE\"/> In his letter \"Marxism and Revolt\" directed to the [[Central Committee of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union|Central Committee of RSDLP(b)]] in September 1917, he putting on the agenda the task of preparing an armed uprising wrote:\n{{cquote|And to treat the revolt in a Marxist way, that is, as an art, we at the same time, without losing a moment, must organize headquarters of the insurgent groups ...}}<ref name=\"GSE\"/>\n\nThe decision of [[Central Committee of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union|Central Committee of RSDLP(b)]] of October 23 and 29, 1917 on enhanced preparation for the armed revolt hastened the creation of uprising bodies at central and local levels. The MRC were elected from representatives of the [[Bolshevik]]s' party, [[workers' council|soviets]], factory or [[soldier committees]], [[Bolshevik Military Organizations]] (Voyenka), [[Red Guards (Russia)|Red Guards]], and others.<ref name=\"GSE\"/> The committees were of various levels such as gubernial, city, county, district, volost; while in the Army were frontlines, army, corps, division, and regimental. On occasions the functions of the Military Revolutionary Committee were performed by [[Revolutionary committee (Soviet Union)|revolutionary committees]]. The military revolutionary committees were not uniform in terms of their social and party composition, however most of them were predominantly represented by [[bolsheviks]].\n\nThe first headquarters of armed uprising became the [[Petrograd Military Revolutionary Committee]] that was created by the [[Petrograd Soviet]] on October 25, 1917.<ref name=\"GSE\"/> Prior to a victorious moment of the uprising in Petrograd, there were over 40 Military Revolutionary Committees in the country the main activity of which was military and technical preparations for the forthcoming revolt.\n\n==List of military revolutionary committees==\nDuring the \"Triumphant advance of Soviet power\" there was a mass establishment of MRCs. Many MRCs appeared on initiative of the arrived delegates of the [[All-Russian Congress of Soviets|2nd All-Russian Congress of Soviets]]. Big squad of commissars, emissaries, agitators was sent to various country's regions by the Petrograd MRC on direction of the [[Central Committee of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union|Central Committee of RSDLP(b)]].<ref name=\"GSE\"/> The Bolshevik's party composed the committees of experienced organizers.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Creation date !! Name !! Head (composition) !! Notes\n|-\n| October 29 || [[Petrograd Military Revolutionary Committee|Petrograd MRC]] || [[Pavel Lazimir]] ([[Andrei Bubnov]], [[Moisei Uritsky]], [[Yakov Sverdlov]], [[Felix Dzerzhinsky]], [[Joseph Stalin]])<ref>David R. Shearer & Vladimir Khaustov, Stalin and the Lubianka: A Documentary History of the Political Police and Security Organs in the Soviet Union, 1922\u20131953\n</ref> || \n|-\n| October 31 || 12th Army MRC || Ya. Cherin ({{ill|Karl Gailis|ru|\u0413\u0430\u0439\u043b\u0438\u0441, \u041a\u0430\u0440\u043b \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}},<ref>[http://www.istoriacccr.ru/gailis_karl_andreevi.html Gailis Karl Andreyevich] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121031103531/http://www.istoriacccr.ru/gailis_karl_andreevi.html |date=2012-10-31 }}</ref> {{ill|J\u0101nis Kr\u016bmi\u0146\u0161-Pil\u0101ts|lv}})<ref>[http://globalpedia.ru/people.php?id=9915&category=55 Krumin, Janis]</ref>|| until November 8, 1917 existed illegally in [[C\u0113sis]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2| November 4 || Estland MRC || {{ill|Ivan Rabchinsky|ru|\u0420\u0430\u0431\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439, \u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}}<ref>[http://bse.sci-lib.com/article094729.html Rabchinsky, Ivan Vasilyevich]. [[Great Soviet Encyclopedia]]</ref> ([[Jaan Anvelt]], [[Viktor Kingissepp]]) || \n|-\n| Pskov MRC || {{ill|Vasili Panyushkin|ru|\u041f\u0430\u043d\u044e\u0448\u043a\u0438\u043d, \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0439 \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0438\u0447}} || Northern Front (from November 8, 1917)\n|-\n| rowspan=2| November 7 || {{ill|Moscow Military Revolutionary Committee|lt=Moscow MRC|ru|\u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0432\u043e\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e-\u0440\u0435\u0432\u043e\u043b\u044e\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442}} || {{ill|Grigory Usievich|ru|\u0423\u0441\u0438\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447, \u0413\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447}} ([[Nikolay Muralov]], {{ill|J\u0101nis Pie\u010de|lv}}, {{ill|Aleksandr Arosev|ru|\u0410\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0432, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440 \u042f\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}}, [[Vladimir Smirnov (politician)|Vladimir Smirnov]])|| \n|-\n| Voronezh revkom || {{ill|Alexey Sergeevich Moiseyev|ru|\u041c\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0435\u0435\u0432, \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0439 \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447}} || \n|-\n| November 8 || Ryazan MRC || {{ill|Arkady Syromyatnikov|ru|\u0421\u044b\u0440\u043e\u043c\u044f\u0442\u043d\u0438\u043a\