{"title_page": "Sreejith Panickar", "text_new": "'''Sreejith Panickar''' is a political analyst, television news debater and writer from [[Kerala]], [[India]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=O'Shea|first=Lizzie|title=Future Histories|publisher=[[Verso Books]]|year=2019|isbn=|location=1788734335, 9781788734332|pages=P159: \"As Sreejith Panickar put it: \"Google got the monopoly of the service without having to bid for it. In effect, the free broadband service was the green flag Google waved to make its entry to our railway stations.\" Panickar predicted that this free access could well end up as a paying service at some point in the future. The company will find a way to make a return on their investment, he argued, through monetizing data or otherwise.\"}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sirfnews.com/netaji-kin-swamy-wrong-about-gumnami-baba/|title=Netaji Kin, Swamy Wrong About Gumnami Baba|last=|first=|date=|website=Sirf News|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mathrubhumi.com/features/social-issues/gumnami-baba-subhash-chandra-bose-netaji-mission-akhilesh-yadav-malayalam-news-1.922675|title=\u0d1a\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02 \u0d09\u0d31\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4b\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d41, \u0d17\u0d41\u0d02\u0d28\u0d3e\u0d2e\u0d3f \u0d2c\u0d3e\u0d2c\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d1f\u0d46 \u0d2a\u0d46\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d33\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d47\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d..|last=|first=|date=|website=Mathrubhumi|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He is the founder-member of Mission Netaji, an Indian [[Nonprofit organization|not-for-profit]] organisation that conducts research on the disappearance of Netaji [[Death of Subhas Chandra Bose|Subhas Chandra Bose]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://old.tehelka.com/no-right-to-information-on-bose/|title=No Right to Information on Bose|last=Naskar|first=Srija|date=|website=Tehelka|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|